  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Helping people move towards reconciliation.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will build knowledge and attitudes for peace within targeted community groups in Sri Lanka, and will enable ethnically or religiously diverse communities to develop a better understanding of each other&apos;s concerns and aspirations, and facilitate them to develop links and constructive relationships with each other. Through building knowledge and establishing local forums for discussion and action, citizens and local government officials will be supported to actively participate in the on-going peace and reconciliation processes put in place by the government in Sri Lanka. Perspectives on peace and reconciliation from the community level will be communicated upwards to national decision-makers, faith leaders, and civil society leaders, and will contribute towards national efforts to develop a common vision for a plural, multi-ethnic and multi-religious society.</narrative>
  </description>
